and we had a really interesting conversation where I said, tell me really what you mean by that.

01:27:23.360 --> 01:27:29.680
Is your argument that I'm using titles that don't actually represent what's in the video?

01:27:30.400 --> 01:27:34.640
No, what's in the title is in the video. I go, okay, so it's not that the title is dishonest.

01:27:34.640 --> 01:27:39.840
Are you saying I'm deliberately picking titles that will garner a larger audience?

01:27:40.480 --> 01:27:42.800
And they said, yeah, that's kind of what I mean. And I said,

01:27:42.800 --> 01:27:46.480
isn't that kind of what we're all doing? The alternative would be choosing titles

01:27:46.480 --> 01:27:50.480
to generate a smaller audience, which seems like a real kind of waste of time. So

01:27:51.600 --> 01:27:55.760
I'm trying to navigate and play the game in a way that's comfortable,

01:27:56.400 --> 01:28:00.160
but use the metrics more as a tool than as something to obsess over.

01:28:00.720 --> 01:28:07.280
Nevertheless, the metrics are what they are and that they are able to affect your psyche.

01:28:08.960 --> 01:28:14.080
It's very difficult, which is why I have a Chrome extension that hides all the views and all that

01:28:14.080 --> 01:28:21.680
on YouTube for me. It's difficult not to let it affect how you think about ideas.

01:28:22.800 --> 01:28:27.280
So maybe your extensive exploration of a particular topic like healthcare

01:28:27.280 --> 01:28:32.400
generated very few views. It's difficult for you to still care about healthcare.

01:28:33.360 --> 01:28:39.440
There's some aspect of the human mind that starts being affected by those views. And I think that's

01:28:39.440 --> 01:28:47.040
a really dangerous thing. Mostly it's probably beneficial because it probably makes you a better

01:28:47.040 --> 01:28:53.200
presenter. If you do care about a topic a lot, you become more charismatic, more you learn

01:28:53.200 --> 01:28:59.440
sort of in Jimmy, Mr. Beast, the way how to present the ideas better. But it also can affect

01:28:59.440 --> 01:29:03.520
which topics you choose to cover, what you choose to think about those topics,

01:29:04.720 --> 01:29:09.360
audience capture those topics. And that's a really scary effect. I'm really worried about my own

01:29:09.360 --> 01:29:16.800
mind in that. So I run from that aggressively. One of the things that I include in my overall

01:29:16.800 --> 01:29:23.040
approaches, I don't think about any one clip. I think about an entire show or a week of shows

01:29:23.040 --> 01:29:30.240
or a month of shows. And so it's less about does anyone clip do well. My view going in is

01:29:30.240 --> 01:29:34.880
I'm going to do stuff that won't do that well, but I think it's really important to do. And I

01:29:34.880 --> 01:29:40.400
want to make it part of my show. And so when I did a clip with 10 ideas for reducing gun violence,

01:29:40.400 --> 01:29:44.720
I know that that's not going to get 500,000 or a million views. I know it's just not going to.

01:29:45.360 --> 01:29:52.160
And the first day it'll get 12,000 and I'll go, I don't care. That's fine. There's a group of people

01:29:52.160 --> 01:29:56.800
in my audience that values this stuff. And I want to keep doing this stuff. I'll end up surprised

01:29:56.800 --> 01:30:03.600
sometime. And two weeks later has 150,000 views because it started being shared. Great. But I

01:30:03.600 --> 01:30:10.320
don't go into it thinking these all need to be home runs by that metric. I always go in saying I

01:30:10.320 --> 01:30:14.880
want to put out a diversity of content, including stuff that is less titillating and salacious,

01:30:14.880 --> 01:30:21.200
but is important to do. It's more researched, etc. And so that's the way I try to resist exactly

01:30:21.280 --> 01:30:25.280
what you're talking about. And I think you have to probably know yourself. For me, metrics,

01:30:25.280 --> 01:30:29.840
I just like numbers too much. And for me, metrics do affect me. That's just why I don't pay attention

01:30:29.840 --> 01:30:36.960
at all. I would love to hire somebody in the team who cares because we currently have folks who

01:30:36.960 --> 01:30:43.360
just all of us just don't care because he probably is good to care enough to kind of just do good

01:30:43.360 --> 01:30:49.280
thumbnails and this kind of stuff to pay attention. But to me personally, I just find inner peace and

01:30:49.280 --> 01:30:56.320
focus if I don't think about the numbers at all. Because I find myself... I just remember a long

01:30:56.320 --> 01:31:04.320
time ago when I started a podcast, I would think that I failed if it didn't do well. Like if I didn't

01:31:04.320 --> 01:31:08.880
celebrate the person well enough, I didn't do a good job enough of a conversation. Well,

01:31:08.880 --> 01:31:14.560
that's not necessarily at all what that means. It's hard not to... This is tough stuff. I mean,

01:31:14.560 --> 01:31:22.160
yeah, I know exactly what you're saying. And part of it is... I mean, it starts in my... You have a

01:31:22.160 --> 01:31:26.800
little bit of a different situation than me because you're doing long form conversations with people

01:31:26.800 --> 01:31:31.520
and the prep is a little bit different. One of the things in my space because I'm reacting mostly

01:31:31.520 --> 01:31:35.360
to what's going on in the news and then also picking topics to dive into a little bit more deeply

01:31:35.920 --> 01:31:41.360
is I have very little control over the news cycle. And there is a meta metric or a macro

01:31:41.360 --> 01:31:47.920
metric that affects me that will quadruple my audience and then take 75% of it away,

01:31:47.920 --> 01:31:54.480
which is the seasonality of election cycles. And the first few election cycles, it's very tough

01:31:54.480 --> 01:32:00.000
because I go, it's October. I'm like, at this rate, we're going to have 20 million subscribers by

01:32:00.000 --> 01:32:06.320
the next... These numbers are unbelievable. And then it's January 30th, the inauguration's over,

01:32:06.880 --> 01:32:12.960
the debate is about the debt ceiling and nothing's going on. And I go, nobody's watching my content.

01:32:12.960 --> 01:32:19.360
I must have forgotten to upload a... Something must be wrong. It's completely beyond my control.

01:32:19.360 --> 01:32:24.320
So I just... And I think part of what you're saying is I try to focus on the things I can control

01:32:24.960 --> 01:32:29.280
and understand those that I really have no control over whatsoever and try not to worry about them.

