running for reelection? Absolutely not. The question about, should there be debates? I would

01:38:37.680 --> 01:38:44.240
like there to be debates. The DNC pretty clearly isn't going to organize them. I think if you did

01:38:44.240 --> 01:38:49.520
them, you would have to say at what polling level do you qualify? And I don't know exactly where you

01:38:49.520 --> 01:38:54.400
put that number. But I think it would be a great thing to put Joe Biden on a stage with, if you

01:38:54.400 --> 01:38:59.280
can get what, 6%, 8%. I'm not really sure what the number would be. I'm totally all for that.

01:39:00.000 --> 01:39:03.600
Why is a set of candidates, at least from my perspective, so weak?

01:39:05.520 --> 01:39:08.480
Do you have an understanding of this? There's a lot of different answers to this.

01:39:10.160 --> 01:39:14.720
One aspect to this, which I think is more of a socio-cultural thing, which I've recently

01:39:14.720 --> 01:39:21.360
read about to some degree, is the job actually turns off the people who would be best at it

01:39:21.360 --> 01:39:24.560
because of what you need to do to become president. And it includes

01:39:25.600 --> 01:39:32.640
all but completely abandoning your existing day-to-day life job, which you may depend on,

01:39:32.640 --> 01:39:40.560
and family to some degree. It's horribly negative, as we already talked about. And at the end of all

01:39:40.560 --> 01:39:45.520
of that, you either lose and then have to rebuild, and maybe you're not in a position to be able to

01:39:45.520 --> 01:39:51.840
do that, or you win. And then now you've got four years of being one of the most hated people,

01:39:51.840 --> 01:39:56.320
no matter how good a job you do. So I think by its nature, it turns off a lot of people that

01:39:56.320 --> 01:40:02.160
would otherwise be good. I also think that there's a lot of posturing from within the parties about,

01:40:02.160 --> 01:40:06.720
well, you might be good, but it's not your time yet, so you should wait. And then let's talk about

01:40:06.720 --> 01:40:10.640
maybe a Senate seat here and there. So it's like a company, essentially, and they're figuring out

01:40:10.640 --> 01:40:15.920
where they want to place people. I think all of these things make it so we end up with candidates

01:40:15.920 --> 01:40:21.360
most people aren't super thrilled with. So it's difficult for somebody who's young or an outsider

01:40:21.360 --> 01:40:28.720
to quickly become a candidate? I think that that's true. And I think also, in a lot of ways, it's

01:40:28.720 --> 01:40:34.080
just not... I mean, would you want to be president? No. I mean, I can't because I wasn't born in the

01:40:34.080 --> 01:40:40.400
U.S., so it's easy for me to say, but... If everyone says no, then we'll get the people that we have.

