03:02:06.080 --> 03:02:13.680
until some pre-negotiated terms are set and the parties to do the negotiating

03:02:14.240 --> 03:02:19.200
are all good faith parties. For example, I don't think Israel's right-wing party,

03:02:19.200 --> 03:02:26.240
Likud, is a particularly good faith arbiter of peace because I think Likud benefits from

03:02:26.240 --> 03:02:31.600
their not being peace and the threat of violence. And there is violence. It's not just the threat

03:02:31.600 --> 03:02:37.680
of violence. I don't think Hamas is going to be an arbiter of peace for the Palestinian people

03:02:37.680 --> 03:02:42.880
either. I think the Palestinian Authority is a question mark. I'm not sure. So I think that

03:02:42.960 --> 03:02:48.800
there need to be some preconditions that would need to be set with regard to everything from

03:02:48.800 --> 03:02:56.320
settlements to a lot of this minutia. Big picture, though, if I imagine what the most likely solution

03:02:56.320 --> 03:03:00.240
looks like, it doesn't mean it's a perfect solution. And obviously, it's a solution many people will

03:03:00.240 --> 03:03:06.480
say it's not going to happen. I think it's a solution where the borders are similar to what

03:03:06.480 --> 03:03:13.600
was being discussed in the Clinton era to some degree. As many of the settlements as possible

03:03:13.600 --> 03:03:18.800
have to go, understanding that some of the bigger ones are just not going to go. And there's going

03:03:18.800 --> 03:03:24.800
to have to be meaningful land swaps with which Yasser Arafat seemed to be amenable to when he

03:03:24.800 --> 03:03:31.680
weighed in on it. I believe it was in the 90s. The topic of the Temple Mount and Jerusalem,

03:03:32.080 --> 03:03:39.360
is a complicated one. But I think that almost certainly East Jerusalem is going to have to be

03:03:39.360 --> 03:03:45.520
part of an eventual Palestinian state. We can go as far as we want to with a lot of this stuff.

03:03:45.520 --> 03:03:50.880
What role does U.S. have to play in this coming to the table with good faith parties?

03:03:50.880 --> 03:03:56.960
I don't know whether I go back and forth between believing that the U.S. should play a big role,

03:03:57.520 --> 03:04:04.560
to the U.S. should play essentially no role whatsoever. Because, of course, of the funding

03:04:04.560 --> 03:04:12.480
of Israel that the U.S. provides, it's not that I have a personal problem with American involvement

03:04:12.480 --> 03:04:16.880
and somebody like Bill Clinton was arguably relatively well positioned to try to make something

03:04:16.880 --> 03:04:22.880
happen. Will it be seen as credible on the global stage? And that's, I think, the most

03:04:22.880 --> 03:04:27.920
important thing. Because at the end of whatever negotiation takes place, both sides need to agree

03:04:27.920 --> 03:04:33.440
that this is where we are renouncing all past claims. And in the future, if there's a disagreement,

03:04:33.440 --> 03:04:37.680
we can't go back to that thing from the 80s or the 90s. That's just like a critical piece of this.

03:04:37.680 --> 03:04:46.480
Yeah. It has to be stable and materialized into something stable over years.

